RAWALPINDI, Sep 25 (APP):Two civilians, including an 8-year old boy, were injured on Friday as Indian Army troops resorted to unprovoked firing at the Line of Control (LoC) in Baroh Sector targeting civil population.
It was 2,340th ceasefire violation by the Indian Army troops in 2020, an Inter Services Public Relations (ISPR) press release said.
